text:
Stagg Street, north side, between Manhattan (left) and Graham (right) Aves., showing from left to right three buildings in the process of demolition which were once in back of buildings No. 153-157 Stagg Street. Upon the sites of these "rookeries" new apartments have been erected. At the right background is seen the N.E. corner of Graham Ave. and Ten Eyck Street.

December 22, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
